heading_context: Volunteer to check standards in prison
chunks.html_content:
Independent Monitoring Boards check the day-to-day standards of prisons - each prison has one associated with it.

You don’t need specific qualifications and you get trained.

Contact the Independent Monitoring Board to volunteer.

heading_context: Volunteer to check standards in prison
chunks.html_content: Volunteering usually takes up about 2 or 3 days per month.
chunks.plain_content:
Volunteer to check standards in prison
How to apply
Volunteering usually takes up about 2 or 3 days per month.

heading_context: Volunteer to check standards in prison
What happens after you return the application pack
chunks.html_content:
You’ll be invited to a tour of the prison and then asked to go for an interview.

If successful, checks are done on your background - this is called ‘security clearance’.

The process can take up to 3 months.
